Template: vigil-agent/key
Type: string
Description: SSH public key provided by vigil hub:
 If you leave this blank, you will need to configure it in
 /etc/vigil-agent.conf before starting Vigil.

Template: vigil-agent/hub_url
Type: string
Description: Vigil hub URL:
 The full URL of the Vigil hub the agent connects to
 (for example https://hub.example.com). The agent will not be started
 automatically until this is set. You can configure it later in
 /etc/vigil-agent.conf.

Template: vigil-agent/token
Type: password
Description: Vigil enrollment or agent token:
 Token used to authenticate this agent to the hub. If you leave this
 blank, you will need to configure it in /etc/vigil-agent.conf.

Template: vigil-agent/docker_access
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Grant the agent access to the Docker socket?
 Adding the vigil user to the "docker" group lets the agent collect
 container inventory and metrics. Membership in that group is equivalent
 to root on this host and effectively bypasses the service sandboxing,
 so only enable it if you need Docker monitoring.
